      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>Industry Applications</h2>
        <div class="application-tags">
          <span>Rubber Roller Systems</span>
          <span>Automation Equipment</span>
          <span>Machine Front Panels</span>
          <span>OEM Components</span>
          <span>Custom Machinery</span>
          <span>Precision Industrial Parts</span>
        </div>
      </section>


      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>Application Scenarios</h2>
        <div class="scenario-list">
          <div class="scenario-item">
            <h3>Cleaning Machine Roller Assembly Housing</h3>
            <p>The front panel of an industrial cleaning machine must securely seat rubber cleaning rollers while withstanding the cyclic loads of continuous roller rotation. Precise CNC milling of the mounting features — bearing seats, clearance holes, and alignment surfaces — ensures consistent roller alignment and prevents the vibration that would degrade cleaning performance and accelerate roller wear.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="scenario-item">
            <h3>OEM Equipment Component Fabrication</h3>
            <p>Machinery manufacturers that outsource precision panel fabrication require components that meet their assembly drawings exactly. Our drawing-based CNC milling service produces front panels to the specified dimensions, tolerances, and surface finishes, whether in small prototype batches or full production volumes, without requiring the OEM to maintain their own machining capacity.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="scenario-item">
            <h3>Replacement and Upgrade Components</h3>
            <p>When aging equipment requires precision panel replacement or when a design revision changes the roller configuration, drawing-based CNC fabrication produces exact replacement or upgraded components without tooling lead times. Material selection can be updated for the replacement run — for example, switching from mild steel to aluminum for weight reduction — while maintaining the original dimensional specification.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>How We Handle Drawing-Based CNC Orders</h2>
        <p>Send us your 2D drawing (DXF/DWG/PDF) or 3D model (STEP/IGES) along with material specification, tolerance requirements, surface finish, and required quantity. We review the drawing for machinability, confirm any ambiguities, and provide a quotation with lead time. Prototype approval samples can be produced before committing to full batch production. Contact us or request a quote to start the process.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-block faq-block">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">What materials can be used for the front panel?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">Material is customized according to your drawing and application requirements. Common choices include aluminum alloy (6061, 6063), stainless steel, carbon steel, and engineering plastics. We will advise on material selection based on load requirements, environment, and weight targets.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">What tolerances can you achieve for this component?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">Achievable tolerances depend on the feature type and material. Typical CNC milling tolerances are ±0.05mm for standard features, with tighter tolerances available for critical bearing seats and alignment surfaces where required by the drawing.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">Do you support prototype quantities before full batch production?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">Yes. We produce prototype quantities for dimensional verification and assembly fit checks before committing to full batch production. This is the standard process for new or revised drawing-based orders.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">Can you match an existing component from a sample rather than a drawing?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">Yes. If you have an existing component but no drawing, we can reverse-measure it and create a drawing for confirmation before machining. Contact us with a description of the component and we will advise on the reverse engineering process.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">What surface finishes are available?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">Available surface finishes include as-machined, anodizing (for aluminum), zinc plating, nickel plating, powder coating, and polishing. Surface finish is specified in the order based on your assembly and functional requirements.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">What is the lead time for batch production?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">Lead time depends on complexity, quantity, and current production schedule. Prototype samples typically take 7–15 working days. Batch production lead times are confirmed at the quotation stage.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

